Made some improvements to the process so it actually generates each triangle properly. Also added comments.

Added the Square class. I'd love to try and make the function call in Main generic enough so I can just swap in and out the shapes I want to generate
And now there are diamonds. Simple Shapes are fun!

Added the baseImage member as well as some functions for setting and clearing it. This member allows me to use the base image as a color palette for the background generator.
Update to the gitignore to ignore the correct directories.

I think this is a decent way of handling the colors. If nothing else it's a pretty good starting place. Admittedly it's my first exposure to programmatically adding components to a UI.

Adding the "Use Image" checkbox. This will make all non-necessary members read only.
Added the ability to load the file and the necessary validations.
Added the ability to export to a specific directory / file name.
Updating the About Page.
